******
[2] Saudi Arabia (Eastern Region): press release 14 May 2013
Date: Tue 14 May 2013
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health Media Center [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/Ministry/MediaCenter/News/Pages/News-2013-05-14-002.aspx


MOH announces detection of 2 new confirmed coronavirus cases in the Eastern Region - 14 May 2013
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Further to its previous statements and within the framework of its continuous monitoring and epidemiological surveillance of coronavirus, the Ministry of Health (MOH) would like to point out that 2 new confirmed cases of coronavirus have been detected among health practitioners in the Eastern Region [Ash Sharqiyah], and they are currently still under the medical observation receiving the proper treatment.

Proceeding from its keenness to provide citizens, journalists, and those who are interested in updated information on coronavirus, MOH would like to expound that they can visit the MOH website which is regularly updated at http://www.moh.gov.sa [in English and Arabic].

It is noteworthy that MOH had already directed a number of medical tips and guidelines to citizens and residents in several ways, including social media, in order to raise the health awareness of this virus and reduce the potential for infection transmission.

For more information, kindly visit the MOH website shown above.

--
